rzon]]\n}}\n{{s-reg|ie}}\n{{s-bef | before = [[Francis William Browne, 4th Baron Kilmaine|The Lord Kilmaine]] }}\n{{s-ttl | title  = [[Representative peer]] for Ireland | years = 1908\u20131925 }}\n{{s-non | reason = Office lapsed}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{UK Conservative Party}}\n{{Leaders of the Opposition UK}}\n{{Foreign Secretary}}\n{{Viceroys of India}}\n{{RGSPresidents}}\n{{Bonar Law Ministry}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Curzon Of Kedleston, George Curzon, 1st Marquess}}\n[[Category:Viceroys of India]]\n[[Category:1890s in British India]]\n[[Category:1900s in British India]]\n[[Category:British diplomats]]\n[[Category:British Secretaries of State for Foreign Affairs]]\n[[Category:British Secretaries of State]]\n[[Category:Lord Presidents of the Council]]\n[[Category:Lords Privy Seal]]\n[[Category:Leaders of the Conservative Party (UK)]]\n[[Category:Members of the Privy Council of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) MPs for English constituencies|Curzon, George]]\n[[Category:Peers of Ireland created by Queen Victoria]]\n[[Category:Irish representative peers]]\n[[Category:Fellows of All Souls College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal Society]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Oxford Union]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Balliol College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Chancellors of the University of Oxford]]\n[[Category:Rectors of the University of Glasgow]]\n[[Category:People educated at Eton College]]\n[[Category:People educated at Wixenford School]]\n[[Category:Knights of the Garter]]\n[[Category:Knights Grand Commander of the Order of the Star of India]]\n[[Category:Knights Grand Commander of the Order of the Indian Empire]]\n[[Category:Lords Warden of the Cinque Ports]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Royal Geographical Society]]\n[[Category:Marquesses in the Peerage of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1886\u20131892|Curzon, George]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1892\u20131895|Curzon, George]]\n[[Category:UK MPs 1895\u20131900|Curzon, George]]\n[