{"title_page": "Gun moll", "text_new": "A '''gun moll''' or '''gangster moll''' is the female companion of a male professional criminal. \"Gun\" was British slang for thief, derived from Yiddish ganef,<ref>{{cite|url=https://ahdictionary.com/word/search.html?q=gun+moll|title=gun moll|work=The American Heritage\u00ae Dictionary of the English Language, Fifth Edition|publisher=Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Publishing Company|year=2019}}</ref> from the Hebrew \"gann\u0101b\" ([[:wiktionary:\u05d2\u05e0\u05d1|\u05d2\u05e0\u05d1]]).<ref>{{cite|url=https://ahdictionary.com/word/search.html?q=GANEF|title=ganef|work=The American Heritage\u00ae Dictionary of the English Language, Fifth Edition|publisher=Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Publishing Company|year=2019}}</ref> .<ref>{\n\n==Prominent gun molls==\n{{example farm|section|date=July 2019}}\n[[File:Helen Julia (Buda) Godman -1919.jpg|thumb|Helen Julia Godman \u2013 Passport photo taken in 1919]]\nProminent, true-life gun molls (and the men they were associated with) include:\n\n* Beulah Baird \u2013 [[Pretty Boy Floyd|Charles Arthur \"Pretty Boy\" Floyd]]\n* [[Mae Capone]] \u2013 [[Al Capone]]\n* Dee David ''(n\u00e9e'' DaLonne Chisam; 1923\u20131976 \u2013 later Cooper, Brumer & Jackson, through four marriages) \u2013 Associated with Frank Niccoli (alias Frankie Burns) (1910\u20131949),<ref>''Long Beach Independent'' \u2013 Long Beach, California \u2013 Wednesday, August 3, 1949 \u2013 p. 23</ref> [[Mickey Cohen]]<ref>''Long Beach Independent'' \u2013 Long Beach, California \u2013 Thursday, July 21, 1949 \u2013 p. 32</ref> and Fred (Alfred Gerardo) Sica (1915\u20131987)<ref>\"California, Death Index, 1940\u20131997,\" index, FamilySearch (https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.1.1/VP2B-9BC), Accessed 24 Aug 2013, Alfred Gerardo Sica, 1987.</ref><ref>''Long Beach Press-Telegram'' \u2013 Long Beach, California \u2013 Friday, November 2, 1956 \u2013 p. 23 (This article points out that DaLonne had actually lived with Fred Sica for a number of years.)</ref> Dee David was an aspiring actress, playing bit-parts in several movies, such as the hat check girl in ''[[Alias a Gentleman]]'' (billed as DaLonne David), and the uncredited role of Rita (the \"Blonde\") in the detective thriller ''Calling Homicide'' (billed as Dalonne Cooper).\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0413403/|title=Dalonne Jackson|website=IMDb}}</ref>\n* Jean Delaney (Crompton) \u2013 [[Tommy Carroll (criminal)|Tommy Carroll]]\n* [[Phoolan Devi]] \u2013 Indian [[dacoit]], gun moll of Vikram Mallah, later turned into the gang leader after his death\n* Victoria DiGiorgio Gotti \u2013 [[John Gotti]]\n* [[Judith Exner]] \u2013 was an [[United States|American]] woman who claimed to be the mistress of [[President of the United States|U.S. president]] [[John F. Kennedy]] and [[American Mafia|Mafia]] leaders [[Sam Giancana]] and [[John Roselli]]\n* [[Evelyn Frechette|Evelyn \"Billie\" Frechette]] \u2013 [[John Dillinger]]\n* [[Buda Godman]] ''(n\u00e9e'' Helen Julia Godman; 1888\u20131945)<ref>[https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:2WGK-WWW \"New York, New York City Municipal Deaths, 1795\u20131949\"] (database), [[FamilySearch]], March 20, 2015<div style=\"margin-left:2em\">\"Helen Daniels,\" [[Date of death|DOD]] \u2013 January 7, 1945; citing Death, [[Queens, New York]], [[New York City Municipal Archives]]; [[Family History Library|FHL]] microfilm ([[Genealogical Society of Utah|GS]] Film No.) 2194201, NYC Queens Reference No. 308 (registration/login may be required, but is free)</ref> \u2013 John Homer T. (\"Dapper Jackie\") French, member of the [[Lou Blonger]] Gang of Denver. A photo of Buda holding a gun is found in Philip S. Van Cise's ''Fighting the Underworld.''<ref>[[Philip S. Van Cise|Van Cise, Philip S.]] ''Fighting the Underworld''. ([[Cambridge, Massachusetts|Cambridge, Mass]].: [[Riverside Publishing|The Riverside Press]], 1936) {{OCLC|435739}}</ref>\n* Catherine Greig \u2013 James [[Whitey Bulger]]\n* Maria Victoria Henao \u2013 [[Pablo Escobar]]\n* Karen Hill \u2013 [[Henry Hill]]\n* [[Virginia Hill]] \u2013 [[Bugsy Siegel]]\n* [[Mary Kinder]] ''(n\u00e9e'' Mary Northern; 1909\u20131981) \u2013 [[Harry Pierpont]]\n* Opal \"Mack Truck\" Long \u2013 [[Russell Clark (criminal)|Russell Clark]]\n* [[Edna Murray]] wife of \"Diamond Joe\" Sullivan, who was executed for murder in 1924. She then married Jack Murray, who was imprisoned for 25 years in 1925. She then lived with [[Volney Davis]], until they were both arrested for kidnapping in 1935. \n* Mary O'Dare \u2013 [[Raymond Hamilton]]\n* [[Bonnie Parker]] \u2013 [[Clyde Barrow]]\n* [[Geri McGee |Geraldine \"Geri\" McGee Rosenthal]] \u2013 [[Frank Rosenthal]]\n* [[Kathryn Kelly | Kathryn Thorne]] ''(n\u00e9e'' Cleo May Brooks; 1904\u20131985) \u2013 [[Machine Gun Kelly|George \"Machine Gun\" Kelly]]\n* Helen Gillis ''(n\u00e9e'' Wawzynak; 1908\u20131987) \u2013 [[Baby Face Nelson|George \"Baby Face\" Nelson]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[Femme fatale]]\n* [[Moll (slang)|Moll]] (Australian slang)\n* [[Pachuco|Pachuca]]\n* [[Ride-or-die chick]]\n* [[Nightclub singer]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wiktionary}}\n\n[[Category:Organized crime members by role]]\n[[Category:Organized crime-related lists]]\n[[Category:Yiddish words and phrases]]\n[[Category:Slang terms for women]]\n[[Category:Female organized crime figures]]\n", "text_old": "A '''gun moll''' or '''gangster moll''' is the female companion of a male professional criminal. \"Gun\" was British slang for thief, derived from Yiddish ganef,<ref>{{cite|url=https://ahdictionary.com/word/search.html?q=gun+moll|title=gun moll|work=The American Heritage\u00ae Dictionary of the English Language, Fifth Edition|publisher=Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Publishing Company|year=2019}}</ref> from the Hebrew \"gann\u0101b\" ([[:wiktionary:\u05d2\u05e0\u05d1|\u05d2\u05e0\u05d1]]).<ref>{{cite|url=https://ahdictionary.com/word/search.html?q=GANEF|title=ganef|work=The American Heritage\u00ae Dictionary of the English Language, Fifth Edition|publisher=Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Publishing Company|year=2019}}</ref> \"Moll\" is also used as a euphemism for a woman prostitute.<ref>{{cite|url=https://ahdictionary.com/word/search.html?q=moll|title=moll|work=The American Heritage\u00ae Dictionary of the English Language, Fifth Edition|publisher=Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Publishing Company|year=2019}}</ref>\n\n==Prominent gun molls==\n{{example farm|section|date=July 2019}}\n[[File:Helen Julia (Buda) Godman -1919.jpg|thumb|Helen Julia Godman \u2013 Passport photo taken in 1919]]\nProminent, true-life gun molls (and the men they were associated with) include:\n\n* Beulah Baird \u2013 [[Pretty Boy Floyd|Charles Arthur \"Pretty Boy\" Floyd]]\n* [[Mae Capone]] \u2013 [[Al Capone]]\n* Dee David ''(n\u00e9e'' DaLonne Chisam; 1923\u20131976 \u2013 later Cooper, Brumer & Jackson, through four marriages) \u2013 Associated with Frank Niccoli (alias Frankie Burns) (1910\u20131949),<ref>''Long Beach Independent'' \u2013 Long Beach, California \u2013 Wednesday, August 3, 1949 \u2013 p. 23</ref> [[Mickey Cohen]]<ref>''Long Beach Independent'' \u2013 Long Beach, California \u2013 Thursday, July 21, 1949 \u2013 p. 32</ref> and Fred (Alfred Gerardo) Sica (1915\u20131987)<ref>\"California, Death Index, 1940\u20131997,\" index, FamilySearch (https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.1.1/VP2B-9BC), Accessed 24 Aug 2013, Alfred Gerardo Sica, 1987.</ref><ref>''Long Beach Press-Telegram'' \u2013 Long Beach, California \u2013 Friday, November 2, 1956 \u2013 p. 23 (This article points out that DaLonne had actually lived with Fred Sica for a number of years.)</ref> Dee David was an aspiring actress, playing bit-parts in several movies, such as the hat check girl in ''[[Alias a Gentleman]]'' (billed as DaLonne David), and the uncredited role of Rita (the \"Blonde\") in the detective thriller ''Calling Homicide'' (billed as Dalonne Cooper).\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0413403/|title=Dalonne Jackson|website=IMDb}}</ref>\n* Jean Delaney (Crompton) \u2013 [[Tommy Carroll (criminal)|Tommy Carroll]]\n* [[Phoolan Devi]] \u2013 Indian [[dacoit]], gun moll of Vikram Mallah, later turned into the gang leader after his death\n* Victoria DiGiorgio Gotti \u2013 [[John Gotti]]\n* [[Judith Exner]] \u2013 was an [[United States|American]] woman who claimed to be the mistress of [[President of the United States|U.S. president]] [[John F. Kennedy]] and [[American Mafia|Mafia]] leaders [[Sam Giancana]] and [[John Roselli]]\n* [[Evelyn Frechette|Evelyn \"Billie\" Frechette]] \u2013 [[John Dillinger]]\n* [[Buda Godman]] ''(n\u00e9e'' Helen Julia Godman; 1888\u20131945)<ref>[https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:2WGK-WWW \"New York, New York City Municipal Deaths, 1795\u20131949\"] (database), [[FamilySearch]], March 20, 2015<div style=\"margin-left:2em\">\"Helen Daniels,\" [[Date of death|DOD]] \u2013 January 7, 1945; citing Death, [[Queens, New York]], [[New York City Municipal Archives]]; [[Family History Library|FHL]] microfilm ([[Genealogical Society of Utah|GS]] Film No.) 2194201, NYC Queens Reference No. 308 (registration/login may be required, but is free)</ref> \u2013 John Homer T. (\"Dapper Jackie\") French, member of the [[Lou Blonger]] Gang of Denver. A photo of Buda holding a gun is found in Philip S. Van Cise's ''Fighting the Underworld.''<ref>[[Philip S. Van Cise|Van Cise, Philip S.]] ''Fighting the Underworld''. ([[Cambridge, Massachusetts|Cambridge, Mass]].: [[Riverside Publishing|The Riverside Press]], 1936) {{OCLC|435739}}</ref>\n* Catherine Greig \u2013 James [[Whitey Bulger]]\n* Maria Victoria Henao \u2013 [[Pablo Escobar]]\n* Karen Hill \u2013 [[Henry Hill]]\n* [[Virginia Hill]] \u2013 [[Bugsy Siegel]]\n* [[Mary Kinder]] ''(n\u00e9e'' Mary Northern; 1909\u20131981) \u2013 [[Harry Pierpont]]\n* Opal \"Mack Truck\" Long \u2013 [[Russell Clark (criminal)|Russell Clark]]\n* [[Edna Murray]] wife of \"Diamond Joe\" Sullivan, who was executed for murder in 1924. She then married Jack Murray, who was imprisoned for 25 years in 1925. She then lived with [[Volney Davis]], until they were both arrested for kidnapping in 1935. \n* Mary O'Dare \u2013 [[Raymond Hamilton]]\n* [[Bonnie Parker]] \u2013 [[Clyde Barrow]]\n* [[Geri McGee |Geraldine \"Geri\" McGee Rosenthal]] \u2013 [[Frank Rosenthal]]\n* [[Kathryn Kelly | Kathryn Thorne]] ''(n\u00e9e'' Cleo May Brooks; 1904\u20131985) \u2013 [[Machine Gun Kelly|George \"Machine Gun\" Kelly]]\n* Helen Gillis ''(n\u00e9e'' Wawzynak; 1908\u20131987) \u2013 [[Baby Face Nelson|George \"Baby Face\" Nelson]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[Femme fatale]]\n* [[Moll (slang)|Moll]] (Australian slang)\n* [[Pachuco|Pachuca]]\n* [[Ride-or-die chick]]\n* [[Nightclub singer]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wiktionary}}\n\n[[Category:Organized crime members by role]]\n[[Category:Organized crime-related lists]]\n[[Category:Yiddish words and phrases]]\n[[Category:Slang terms for women]]\n[[Category:Female organized crime figures]]\n", "name_user": "195.204.197.111", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gun_moll"}
